com.nymph.transaction.requestevent

Class WaitCardRequestEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nymph.transaction.TransactionActionEvent
      • com.nymph.transaction.TransactionActionRequestEvent
        • com.nymph.transaction.requestevent.WaitCardRequestEvent

  • public class WaitCardRequestEvent
extends TransactionActionRequestEvent
    Emv before wait card event.

    Once the event is triggered, you can show the request card ui to direct the user to swipe/insert/swing cards.

    There is no need to call request card interface for ic card. The emv core will do this for you.

    Created by feiq on 2017/3/8.
